Quote: With visions of the colony being overtaken by the "Yellow Peril" or "Mongolian Horde", the government, in 1881, passed a law making Chinese migrants pay a poll tax of GBP10 before they could enter New Zealand... The situation improved with the abolition of the poll tax in 1944.
